VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription:
Probably the nicest 34 you will find....Up dated interior, professionally maintained teak and paint.. rigged with New Raymarine fishfinder/ GPS ,outriggers and removable bait tank.

The 34' Marshal designed Californian sedan cruisers are built for cruising and fishing the coastal waters of the Pacific. Equipped with twin 220 hp Caterpillar diesels this boat cruises easily at 12 knots with a top speed of 18 knots readily available. At cruising speeds the 300 gallon fuel capacity provides a maximum range of 400 miles. Fitted with upper and lower helm stations, comfortable flying bridge seating, a nice cockpit for fishing & lounging, and a comfortable interior suitable for extended stays aboard with two sleeping cabins, the Californian 34 is indeed a very dependable and versatile boat.

Handsome lines, stoutly built and easily handled, the Californian 34 is a popular classic. This particular Californian 34 is well maintained and the motivated seller is ready to move on to his next boat.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
The Donzi 35 ZF is a high-performance center console fisherman
for anglers who place a premium on flat-out speed and agility.The cuddy configuration will sleep 2 and the 35 ZF boasts a large center console with an enclosed head and shower.

There's a lockable electronics box, A pair of big fish
boxes are built into the deck on either side of the dual drop down helm seats., a freshwater sink, an oval recirculating livewell, a transom door, a cockpit shower, ample storage, and more.

The 35 ZF also has Donzi's wide beam, Z-Tech stepped hull, and enough speed to smoke anything on the water.


Forward, molded steps provide easy access to the cabintop that
serves as a casting platform.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Entertainment comes naturally on the 400 Sundancer, with an open floorplan that creates generous, interconnected social zones throughout the boat. Large windows and a convenient sunroof, part of Sea Ray's SkyFlow Design™ philosophy, let in an abundance of natural light. Rich materials and finishes enhance aesthetics as well as comfort, while two full-beam staterooms invite you and your guests to relax, settle in and savor the full experience of life on the water.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Super Air Nautique 230, PCM ZR4 MPI, Nautique Configurable Running Surface with automated Hydro-Gate, waste receptacle, Nautique Surf System with WAVEPLATE, Wake package with 1300 lbs. of integrated ballast, Flight control tower with rotating wakeboard/wakesurf racks, Surf pipe exhaust, Cleats (4), LED courtesy lights, Cooler (removable softside), Zero off GPS, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Towable mooring cover, 1 Pair 7.7 JL tower speakers, Surf Select with Surf Switch, Tandem axle trailer.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Let the Super Air Nautique 230 lead you on a path to the realization of what you truly want in a wake boat. From the rigorous demands of competition to the simplicity of pure enjoyment on the water, the 230 accepts the challenge to perform without hesitation. The route to finding yourself begins here, so put the throttle down and embrace the journey.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique 230 hull is contest proven and die-hard approved. Traditional design features blend perfectly with new-age ideas and technology that result in a boat with precise handling, a pro-level wakeboard wake and massive surf wave. Our Nautique Surf System is seamlessly integrated into the hull for a fully-customizable wave that will blow you away.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Surf System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique Surf System® (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Our JL Audio stereo system delivers the best sound in the industry tuned perfectly for your Nautique boat. The Super Air Nautique 230 comes standard with four JL MX-Series speakers. Upgrade to the MX-Series Premier package which adds two more JL MX-Series speakers and a 10” subwoofer driven by a 6-channel amplifier to make it complete. Turn it up behind the boat with the choice of our 6x9 RMA/Focal or premium JL M-Series 7.7” tower speakers.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique G25, XR7 Supercharged MPI 6.2L, Design package, Walk-thru air dam door, Battery maintenance system, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Retractable bow arm rests, Bow filler cushion, Freshwater engine flush system, Enhanced courtesy light package, Towable/Mooring cover, LINC Panoray Navionics Map, Platform cover, Two pair of JL audio 8.8 tower speakers, Ultra premium steering wheel in hand stitched leather, M Series studio elite stereo with Wavefront technology, Surf select with surf switch, Triple axle trailer.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Interior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Stepping into a Super Air Nautique G25 is an experience that puts luxury, comfort, and space beyond comprehension. We have moved into a new realm of design for 2017 with a unique, open helm that puts abstract form into perfect function. The all-new 12.4” LINC PANORAY touchscreen puts intuitive control at your fingertips along with menu customization in our new switchboard feature. All-new colors give your G25 interior a unique style with seating for nineteen so bring your family, bring your friends, and enjoy the ride of a lifetime.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Exterior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Exude power with exquisite styling on a grand scale in the Super Air Nautique G25. For 2017, our G-series flight control tower features all-new styling that emphasizes aggression with strength and functionality. Stay unique with our new white chromax and gel coat color options to deliver more customization to our largest canvas. Add our Galaxy or new Surf graphics and stand out like no one else on the water.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: BUILT ON A DREAM
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G25 takes the legendary G-Series platform to a place that leaves nothing behind while leaving everything else in its wake. Built on a dream that brings everyone along, experiences on the water only get better when shared. Large waterways are open for endless adventure so grab everyone, get in, and GO!

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: PERFORMANCE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G25 takes our legendary G-series performance to twenty-five feet with precision handling and the wake and wave that have defined a new generation. Creating an ideal experience for everyone on the boat, the G-series was custom-tailored to every level of riding and surfing realizing the pinnacle of design and technology with no rival.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: SOUND
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique and JL Audio have created the best audio systems in the industry with engineered sound that is unmatched on the water. The M-Series Elite package comes standard on the Super Air Nautique G25 featuring 6-JL M-Series speakers and a 10” subwoofer powered by an 8-channel amplifier. Our optional M-Series Studio Elite package steps up for 2017 with two 12” subwoofers and includes the G23 and G25 exclusive JL WaveFront™ technology featuring JL 6.5” M-Series speakers firing through a specially-tuned aperture at the base of the windshield. This premium sound package also features zone control to configure sound throughout your boat just the way you like it.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: ENGINE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G25 comes standard with industry-leading direct-injection from PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology in our H6DI engine. For even more power, supercharge your ride with the XR7 and XS7 engine options. Our 2.0:1 transmission comes standard on all G-series models delivering smooth operation matched with the perfect combination of horsepower and torque.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: HULL
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G-Series hull design has revolutionized the industry proving that it is possible to optimize wake and wave shape for all skill levels and line lengths. Wakeboarders from beginner to pro look to the legendary wake and wave of our G-series boats when pushing themselves and the sport to new levels. Our Nautique Configurable Running Surface (NCRS) is seamlessly integrated to fine-tune the hull under every condition along with 2,850 pounds of sub-floor ballast to customize the experience for every rider. The Nautique Surf System is designed into the hull to work in concert with hull features and the NCRS to create a fully-adjustable, perfectly-shaped wave on either side of the boat in seconds.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique Surf System® (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine-tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: WARRANTY
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
A Reputation Built On Quality And Integrity

For over 92 years Nautique has built a reputation on the quality of our products and the integrity of our word. True value is created in each precious moment you spend on the water in our boats and we want to ensure you have the best ownership experience possible. When you join the Nautique family, you can rest easy knowing that we take care of our own backing your boat with the Nautique 5-Year Transferable Warranty*

*Nautique warrants to the original user or purchaser, whichever comes first, that each new Nautique boat, as originally manufactured by Nautique, shall under normal authorized use be free of defect in material and workmanship for a period of five (5) years or 500hrs from the date of delivery (whichever comes first). This warranty applies to factory installed components including boat parts, options or other components not manufactured by Nautique Boat Company.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique G25, XR7 Supercharged MPI 6.2L, Enhanced courtesy lighting package, Two pair of 8.8 JL Audio M-series speakers, Bimini with tower mounted surf pockets, Integrated dual battery with charger, Platform and mooring cover, Automatic fire extinguisher, Freshwater engine flush system, Heater with defroster, Nautique integrated steering assist, Phender pro, Surf select with surf switch, Ultra premium hand stitched steering wheel, Walk through air damn door, Retractable bow armrest, Bow filler cushion, Heated driver and love seat, Boat mate trailer

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Interior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Stepping into a Super Air Nautique G25 is an experience that puts luxury, comfort, and space beyond comprehension. We have moved into a new realm of design for 2017 with a unique, open helm that puts abstract form into perfect function. The all-new 12.4” LINC PANORAY touchscreen puts intuitive control at your fingertips along with menu customization in our new switchboard feature. All-new colors give your G25 interior a unique style with seating for nineteen so bring your family, bring your friends, and enjoy the ride of a lifetime.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Exterior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Exude power with exquisite styling on a grand scale in the Super Air Nautique G25. For 2017, our G-series flight control tower features all-new styling that emphasizes aggression with strength and functionality. Stay unique with our new white chromax and gel coat color options to deliver more customization to our largest canvas. Add our Galaxy or new Surf graphics and stand out like no one else on the water.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: BUILT ON A DREAM
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G25 takes the legendary G-Series platform to a place that leaves nothing behind while leaving everything else in its wake. Built on a dream that brings everyone along, experiences on the water only get better when shared. Large waterways are open for endless adventure so grab everyone, get in, and GO!

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: PERFORMANCE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G25 takes our legendary G-series performance to twenty-five feet with precision handling and the wake and wave that have defined a new generation. Creating an ideal experience for everyone on the boat, the G-series was custom-tailored to every level of riding and surfing realizing the pinnacle of design and technology with no rival.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: SOUND
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique and JL Audio have created the best audio systems in the industry with engineered sound that is unmatched on the water. The M-Series Elite package comes standard on the Super Air Nautique G25 featuring 6-JL M-Series speakers and a 10” subwoofer powered by an 8-channel amplifier. Our optional M-Series Studio Elite package steps up for 2017 with two 12” subwoofers and includes the G23 and G25 exclusive JL WaveFront™ technology featuring JL 6.5” M-Series speakers firing through a specially-tuned aperture at the base of the windshield. This premium sound package also features zone control to configure sound throughout your boat just the way you like it.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: ENGINE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G25 comes standard with industry-leading direct-injection from PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology in our H6DI engine. For even more power, supercharge your ride with the XR7 and XS7 engine options. Our 2.0:1 transmission comes standard on all G-series models delivering smooth operation matched with the perfect combination of horsepower and torque.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: HULL
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G-Series hull design has revolutionized the industry proving that it is possible to optimize wake and wave shape for all skill levels and line lengths. Wakeboarders from beginner to pro look to the legendary wake and wave of our G-series boats when pushing themselves and the sport to new levels. Our Nautique Configurable Running Surface (NCRS) is seamlessly integrated to fine-tune the hull under every condition along with 2,850 pounds of sub-floor ballast to customize the experience for every rider. The Nautique Surf System is designed into the hull to work in concert with hull features and the NCRS to create a fully-adjustable, perfectly-shaped wave on either side of the boat in seconds.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique Surf System® (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine-tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: WARRANTY
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
A Reputation Built On Quality And Integrity

For over 92 years Nautique has built a reputation on the quality of our products and the integrity of our word. True value is created in each precious moment you spend on the water in our boats and we want to ensure you have the best ownership experience possible. When you join the Nautique family, you can rest easy knowing that we take care of our own backing your boat with the Nautique 5-Year Transferable Warranty*

*Nautique warrants to the original user or purchaser, whichever comes first, that each new Nautique boat, as originally manufactured by Nautique, shall under normal authorized use be free of defect in material and workmanship for a period of five (5) years or 500hrs from the date of delivery (whichever comes first). This warranty applies to factory installed components including boat parts, options or other components not manufactured by Nautique Boat Company.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Time to get serious. Real serious. Dare we say that once you test ride the 244 Xtreme you'll never seriously consider an inboard tow boat again. Adjustable dual prop stern drive power and Chaparral's deep-V bottom design combine to create the optimum wake for riders of all levels. Go ahead, take out some lip or add some height. Behind the wheel, you'll marvel at the slow speed stability, cornering agility and ease of control. Fuel economy? The 244 annihilates inboards of comparable length and enjoys an even more distinct advantage at top-end. Inside, we really gain an edge on the inboards with an enclosed head, standard Bimini top, excellent legroom and massive storage. No pretender, the 244 is setup for pro-level competition with standard Perfect Pass, forward ballast, a customtower and the largest swim platform in this size range.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription:
This is a prime example of what Meridian Motor Yachts were made for. High end condo on the water, at an affordable price. This beautiful yacht has been well maintained by her owners, and has been in fresh water for its whole life, until a year and a half ago. She also has bow and stern thrusters from SidePower, which makes her easy to handle in tight slips.

This boat is in Sunroad Marina in San Diego and can be shown at anytime. This is an absolute must see if you are in the market for an aft cabin style yacht!!!

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: With a hull design that maximizes performance and a deck design that optimizes space, the Meridian 408's aft cabin configuration has plenty of room for family and friends. Exceptional interior visibility gives everyone views of the magnificent surroundings. A full-beam salon lets you entertain with ease, while the salon media center features a 24-inch television, VCR, AM/FM stereo and CD player to deliver entertainment in style. A forward head can be accessed from the forward stateroom and salon, for use as a day head. A full-beam master stateroom with regular queen innerspring mattress lets you sleep in luxurious comfort.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique 226 is well on its way to redefining the standards in the pleasure boat market. From the nimble responsiveness and precision handling of this V-drive model to the spacious open bow with its sculpted upholstery and the ever-present cavernous storage, this ultra runabout is perfect for both cruising and skiing. In fact, even thrill-seeking riders are sure to find an extreme wake behind the Nautique 226. Choose the Team Package and the 226 will come equipped with rear and center ballast as well as a Flight Control Tower, Prefect Pass Digital pro, and so much more. With room for up to 12 family and friends, big is the operative word for this luxury liner. Highly attractive appointments include the expansive sunpad and optional table that quickly converts the open bow or main seating section into a cozy dining area.

Entertainment comes naturally on the 400 Sundancer, with an open floorplan that creates generous, interconnected social zones throughout the boat. Large windows and a convenient sunroof, part of Sea Ray's SkyFlow Design™ philosophy, let in an abundance of natural light. Rich materials and finishes enhance aesthetics as well as comfort, while two full-beam staterooms invite you and your guests to relax, settle in and savor the full experience of life on the water.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription:
THIS IS AS CLOSE TO NEW AS YOU WILL EVER FIND

2016 Meridian 391 SB, Mojave tan hull, Black canvas, Int. Sys 1 - white/tan, T QSB 6.7L 425 T3 DTS Diesels, Tan Colored hull upgrade,Sat TV with 2 additional Flat screens, Mocha - solid surface counter tops, Interior carpet runners, Salon ice maker, Master stateroom entertainment system, Hide-a-bed, Central vacuum system, AC/Heat, Overboard discharge with macerator, Diesel generator, Full canvas w/exterior carpet, Large fiberglass table option - bridge, Cockpit to bridge door, Cockpit speakers, Raw water washdown fore & aft, Raymarine auto pilot - bridge, Raymarine premium navigation pack, Oil change system.Underwater Lights

This boat is shown by appointment only  Call Dan

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Knowing that some family cruisers look like minivans, Meridian designed its 391 Sedan to bring the styling and performance of a sportscar to the class without losing any practical features. This attractive yacht's sleek profile conceals a wide-open salon with warm cherry-wood interior, premium-gloss finish, homelike seating arrangements and 360-degree views of the horizon. She also features a dedicated dinette and fully-equipped galley that are seamlessly integrated into the main living space, two large staterooms and separate shower and head compartments, each with its own vanity and sink. The flybridge's distinctive overhang offers more space topside as well as cockpit weather protection, and its molded-in steps are hinged to provide direct engine-room access. Why settle for a floating box on the water when you can enjoy all the style, performance and comfort of the 391.

Key Features:

  • Two stateroom layout with island berths
  • Relaxed, molded staircase to bridge
  • Extended bridge with seating for eight
  • Stand-up access to engine room
  • Ultra-flow™ Comfort Air System
  • Standard cockpit seating
  • Concealed anchor locker
  • Integrated Vessel Control (IVC)

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription:
This is a West Coast fishermans dream ! Absolutly ready to fish !!

Don't sit there dreaming...the seller is motivated and it won't last long.....

Twin  250 hp 4 strokes, full tower with controls and elecrtonics , Autopilot with remote for tower, 4 kw Diesel Generator, Air and Heat, Removable Pacific Edge 3 scoop bait tank +  a 1 scoop corner tank, Garmin electronics, fish lockers , Outriggers,Underwater LED lights, LED flood lights , Fusion stereo with sub 

PLUS you get the solid ride of the Boston Whaler's Unsinkable Legend

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
The extensive electronics package includes color display with radar, GPS chart plotter, fish finder and marine VHF radio.  Other features include the Smart Craft display with fuel consumption, engine monitoring and diagnostics, diesel generator with sound shield, batteries,  factory hardtop, canvas package, down rigger outlets and lots of built-in fishing equipment.A full galley with stove, oven refrigerator, sink, hot water and lots of storage. There is sleeping for four and a dinette for mealtime. The 305 Conquest boasts an impressive 58 square feet of cockpit space and is a perfectly balanced design for both fish fighting or entertaining. Its helm deck area is elevated for superior visibility fore and aft. The recessed bow walk-around provides more secure-feeling access to the anchor locker and bow area. The cabin interior is warm and inviting, thanks to rich accoutrements including cherry cabinetry, granite-colored countertops and decorator vinyls and accents. You don’t have to sacrifice comfort for fishability.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: 350 Coupe
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Introducing the Sundancer 350 Coupe, an exciting new addition to Sea Ray's most iconic series. With a sleek hardtop and enhanced coupe foredeck seating/lounging zone, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is a brilliant entertaining platform and an inviting place to spend entire days on the water. Premium amenities, state-of-the-art technology and unrivaled performance - with your choice of sterndrive or inboard propulsion - combine to deliver a fully enjoyable cruising experience. Options for customization abound, meaning you can make the Coupe totally your own. And with a sleek, stylish aesthetic that's both gorgeously modern and unmistakably Sea Ray, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is a boat you'll be proud to own and proud to share.

With a sleek hardtop and enhanced coupe foredeck seating/lounging zone, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is a brilliant entertaining platform and an inviting place to spend entire days on the water. Premium amenities, state-of-the-art technology and unrivaled performance - with your choice of sterndrive or inboard propulsion - combine to deliver a fully enjoyable cruising experience. Options for customization abound, meaning you can make the Coupe totally your own. And with a sleek, stylish aesthetic that's both gorgeously modern and unmistakably Sea Ray, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is a boat you'll be proud to own and proud to share.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Craftsmanship
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
A better cruise

When a marine engine generates energy, the boat’s design determines how efficiently that energy converts to forward motion. The Sundancer 350 Coupe’s hull is specifically designed to work with this transfer, actually amplifying the amount of usable energy for a smoother, more powerful ride. Sea Ray makes your boat work smarter not harder, so you can get the most out of your Sundancer.

 

Details matter

A car tire out of alignment—even by a fraction of an inch—forces the driver to constantly correct for a straight drive. Incorrect alignment by even a tenth of an inch on a boat causes the same disturbance in your ride’s smoothness and ease of handling. You shouldn’t have to settle on the water. Sea Ray uses cutting-edge robotic equipment to measure, cut and drill for engine placement that’s within four thousandths of an inch of true—about the thickness of a sheet of paper—to ensure every Sea Ray drives as perfectly as it was meant to.

 

The future of boating

Next Wave is an aggressive commitment to innovation across all Sea Ray platforms. The goal is nothing short of reimagining the boating experience again and again. By developing and championing new technologies such as Quiet Ride™, Dynamic Running Surface™ and Digital Dash™, and design breakthroughs including SkyFlow Design™, Sea Ray is asserting itself as the dominant global presence and a company of forward thinkers.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Design
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Bringing the outside in

The Sundancer 350 Coupe is designed for the outdoors, and its oversized hullside windows help bring the outside in, making the cabin airy and bright. Multi-tone accents and durable, marine-grade vinyl with UV-protection technology are more than just finishing touches on the Sundancer Series, they highlight Sea Ray’s signature style.

 

Space by design

The Sundancer 350 Coupe boasts impressive capacity for more entertaining and more memories thanks to clever design that maximizes onboard space and delivers more comforts than ever before. An extended swim platform and optional transom gourmet center bring the party all the way down to the water.

 

The Sea Ray way

Better materials make a better boat, and that’s why Sea Rays are the best. Teak accents elevate the stairs and footrest on the port lounge, while the helm is impeccably dressed for ergonomics and good looks. From the solid-surface wetbar countertop with stainless-steel trim to the enclosed interior head with a full fiberglass shower, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is done to the nines.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Features
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Delicious details

From the deluxe galley with ample storage to the solid-surface counter tops and recessed stove, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is fit for a top chef. The optional transom gourmet center can also accommodate a fridge, speakers, and built-in grill, so al fresco dining is both glamorous and convenient. Now, entertaining on your boat is easy as pie.

Sweet dreams

The Sundancer 350 Coupe’s V-berth comes fully equipped so you can rest easy. The double bed is outfitted with neutral sheets as well as a luxurious memory-foam mattress. Created by NASA, memory foam delivers undisturbed comfort for full rest. When you sleep well, you can wake up refreshed and ready for another beautiful day on the water.

Kings of comfort

The needs of you and your guests may change from outing to outing. That's why the Sundancer 350 Coupe includes Modelsiad spaces to settle in and get comfortable, from the inviting salon, to the mid-berth convertible twin beds, to the roomy V-berth with ample storage and an island-style double bed. Your boat's interior should fit your needs, and the Sundancer 350 Coupe is designed to do just that.

Stay onboard

Maximize your comfort on the water. The cabin's full fiberglass head features separate stalls for the shower and the head and sink, adding convenience when guests are aboard. Premium refinements and upscale fit and finish are pleasing to the eye and the touch, helping you make even more of a day of it, no matter how far you travel from the dock.

 

At the forefront of foredecks

Now this is clever: The Sundancer 350 Coupe features innovative new foredeck seating, expanding the usage possibilities beyond anything you've seen before on a coupe model. A recessed bow lounger seating system includes an articulating backrest, beverage holders and integral speakers. So you can enjoy the open air from a whole new perspective.

 

  • Expanded Flybridge with social layout
  • Spacious interior with Galley-Aft layout
  • Standard Raymarine® eS12 widescreen chartplotter, with radar, at upper & lower helms
  • Full beam master stateroom with plenty of storage
  • Superior sun coverage w/optional hardtop & foredeck shade
  • Power actuated aft seat expands cockpit space
  • Available Flybridge Enclosure with Air Conditioning & Heating

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Warranty
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Count on Sea Ray’s 3-Year Factory Warranty

One of the primary benefits of a new boat purchase is the freedom to relax, to put aside worry and focus on savoring the well-lived life on the water. Accordingly, Sea Ray is proud to offer a stellar 3-year factory warranty. This program, Sea Ray SENTIN3L, provides 3 years of enhanced coverage on every new cruiser, sport yacht and yacht in the Sea Ray lineup. The end result? Exceptional peace of mind.

All 2018 Sea Ray cruisers, sport yachts and yachts feature Sea Ray’s 3-year, bow-to-stern factory warranty on the boat and its components from defects in materials and workmanship. Additionally, gas engines are covered by a 5-year warranty backed by Mercury and Brunswick Product Protection, while diesel engines receive the coverage defined by their manufacturer. Finally, beyond the 3-year bow-to-stern coverage, all cruisers, sport yachts and yachts also have a 10-year Structural Hull Limited Warranty.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Make a splash without rocking the boat: The SDX 270 is geared for incredible stability, comfort and handling. Sea Ray's purpose-driven engineering encompasses everything from a precision-molded hull right down to details like helm visors that minimize glare on gauges, and optional, soft, SeaDek swim platform matting underfoot. So for passengers of all ages looking to carve wake, catch up with loved ones or simply catch rays, the SDX 270 inspires lasting impressions.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: A truly excellent on-water experience starts with more. More friends, more family, more room, more power, more ease and more fun. The Sea Ray SLX 350 delivers in every sense. Yacht Certified and a standard wet bar with refrigerator make entertaining a must. An array of Sea Ray's Next Wave™ innovations-from the noise-quashing powers of Quiet Ride™ to the precision and stability of Dynamic Running Surface to the agility of Axius® joystick technology-take the experience to the next level. And a host of intelligent features combine in a sleek, stylish package that exceeds all expectations. In short, the SLX 350 will make you want to spend even more time on the water.

• A superior ride & handling is further enhanced with optional Axius® Propulsion
  • System w/joystick control and Dynamic Running Surface™
  • Revolutionary styling is accentuated by extended hull side windows and luxury-auto style upholstery
  • Best-In-Class seating layout includes seating for 18 anchored by ergonomic, convertible aft loungers
  • Plenty of Sun coverage via fiberglass hardtop w/optional extended sunshade
  • Innovations, such as unique storage solutions throughout the interior and proprietary quietRIDE™ Technology - featuring Tuned Transom®, enhance the boater's experience
  • Next Wave features are available for customization - including a Digital Dash and enhanced lighting package

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The 24 MXZ flaunts the largest combination of bow and cockpit space in our lineup and kicks a meaty wake and long, clean wakesurf wave as well. Most will opt for SURF GATE, to allow for surfing on each side of your evenly-weighted vessel. Add 1,450 pounds of hard-tank ballast and drop the Power Wedge to maximize your experience, while your crew sits deep in the most luxurious of interiors. Flip up the seat backs to experience our Wakeview™ seating and enjoy conveniences like a removable, full-size cooler. Expect the same performance Malibu is known for, as this is the best performing 24-foot boat in its class – especially on big lakes with variable water conditions.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description

So for passengers of all ages looking to carve wake, catch up with loved ones or simply catch rays, the SDX 270 inspires lasting impressions.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Classic heritage meets cutting-edge capability in the 170 Montauk. This nimble center console model retains its clean, timeless aesthetic and rugged “hose-and-go” utility while providing enhanced comfort, performance and versatility. Count on all the features you need to get the job done, and the impeccable quality you know to expect from Boston Whaler — and fall in love all over again with the 170 Montauk.

  •    Convenient new integrated forward fishbox with overboard drain.
  •    Optional Fishing Package includes tackle drawers, console-mounted rod holders, and 72-quart cooler seat with cushion and backrest.
  •    Standard 90-hp Mercury® Command Thrust FourStroke engine.
  •    Integrated 25-gallon fuel tank for added range.
  •    Available Raymarine® navigation and fishfinding electronics including RealVision 3D.
  •    Optional Teak Package adds stylish teak boarding steps and swim ladder flooring.
  •    Standard galvanized trailer with swing tongue, disc brakes and LED lights for safe, easy transport.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: Extremely clean low hours and well maintained. Updated electronics, Caterpillar  engines with recent cooling system service.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The splendid Sea Ray 510 Sundancer is turning heads the world over. As part of the proud Sundancer line, this yacht was created for performance and style. The cabin of the 510 Sundancer has only the finest interior finishes hand-picked by Sea Ray. Consider the granite-look Corian countertops, Vitricor wood trim in either cherry or clear maple finishes, and the deep-pile stain-resistant carpet. A concealed floor storage compartment in the galley allows stowage of extra gear without detracting from the contemporary decor. The master stateroom has a queen-size bed with innerspring mattress, an entertainment center and a luxurious head with a VacuFlush toilet, Corian sink and countertop and cultured marble floor. A full-size bed with an upper bunk and a guest head area with dual entry doors makes the guest stateroom perfect for family traveling. A pit group sofa with an electric slide-out bed serves as the focal point of the salon, where there's also a satellite ottoman that converts to a dining or cocktail table. The galley has a recessed three-burner cooktop, a refrigerator with freezer, microwave - convection oven, Spacemaker coffee maker and a mini bar that slides out at the touch of a button. Everything needed for extended cruises has been included without sacrificing the comforts of home, right down to a standard washer and dryer combination. The salon entertainment center features a color TV, VCR and Clarion AM-FM digital cassette and CD stereo system with a six-disc CD changer and six speakers. The entire cabin is kept comfortable year-round by a 31,000 BTU air conditioning and heating system. Above, the cockpit has a definite European flare with a sport spoiler, flip-up thigh-rise helm seat and Euro-styled companion bench seat. The U-shaped cockpit seating area with a hi-lo fiberglass table features an electrically retractable sunpad. A curved tri-section tinted-glass windshield with power vent creates an unobstructed view while increasing air flow to the helm and cockpit. Entertaining on board the 510 Sundancer is a sheer joy with a standard wetbar, icemaker, snap-in carpet liner, aft sun shade and a second Clarion AM-FM digital cassette stereo with six-disc CD changer, subwoofer, four speakers and a cockpit remote control. It's easy to overlook the abundant storage in the port and starboard panels and in the aft deck fender storage compartment. From bow to stern, this yacht was engineered for accessibility. Molded steps and a walk-through transom make passage easy in and around the boat. Even access to the bilge has been simplified with a gas-assisted service hatch and a stainless steel ladder. Serious technical systems also abound on the 510 Sundancer. Check the hydraulic power steering with the tilt wheel, the Raytheon electronics package, the Glendinning cablemaster with remote, the Lofrans Progress II all-chain windlass with its dedicated chain storage hatch, and the 11 kW Westerbeke generator inside its own sound box. Twin 582 horsepower Caterpillar V-drives ensure a smooth ride while an engine synchronizer keeps RPMs at an optimum level for better fuel efficiency. There are also twin diesel V-drive options as well as a generator upgrade, additional electronics and other options to further enhance the yacht's performance.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Get used to the stares, because the SLX 230 is sleek, powerful, cutting-edge and completely crush-worthy. You and your guests won't mind, settled into the perfectly accommodating bow or expansive transom lounge. And it's not like you won't share the fun. With capacity for 13, the SLX 230 is the consummate host's perfect party platform. When ready to shift from chilling to running, goose the MerCruiser® power, let the optional Dynamic Running Surface™ perfect your attitude and encourage wakeboarders to throw tantrums. A perfectly composed boat can pump up the adrenaline, too.

Key Features
  • Standard with MerCruiser's new 4.5-liter 250HP Bravo® III Sterndrive Engine
  • Comfortably seats 12 people while underway
  • Expansive cockpit space
  • Transom seating with transformable backrest
  • Luxurious and plush seating, with abundant storage beneath
  • Optional state-of-the-art equipment such as Submersible Manual Swim Platform; Watersports Tower; Touch Screen Dynamic Electronics Display; Dynamic Running Surface™; etc.
  • Iconic styling with elegant hull sculpting, available in multiple color configurations

When ready to shift from chilling to running, goose the MerCruiser® power, let the optional Dynamic Running Surface™ perfect your attitude and encourage wakeboarders to throw tantrums. A perfectly composed boat can pump up the adrenaline, too.

  • Standard with MerCruiser's new 4.5-liter 250HP Bravo® III Sterndrive Engine
  • Comfortably seats 12 people while underway
  • Expansive cockpit space
  • Transom seating with transformable backrest
  • Luxurious and plush seating, with abundant storage beneath
  • Optional state-of-the-art equipment such as Submersible Manual Swim Platform; Watersports Tower; Touch Screen Dynamic Electronics Display; Dynamic Running Surface™; etc.
  • Iconic styling with elegant hull sculpting, available in multiple color configurations

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription:
Proven Fishing Machine With ALL The Add-Ons!!!!!

This Boston Whaler 210 Montauk has everything. Raymarine Radar, Chart Plotter, and Auto Pilot. Rigged exclusively for West Coast Fishing with a t-top to get out of the sun, livewell with raw water pump, and trim tabs. She is ready to go! Trailer registration is current, and so is the boat. Title in hand. The owners are ready to sell!

Boston Whaler has made a name for itself as the most sea worthy vessel out there. It's really rare to come across a used Whaler for sale that is this clean and well equipped. People generally hold on to them through multiple generations. Take the opportunity to own the unsinkable legend today!

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The 210 Montauk takes the classic center-console Boston Whaler platform to new levels of performance and possibility. Its standard boat-motor-trailer package includes a 150-hp Mercury FourStroke, allowing you to go farther offshore and stay out longer. The size gains create an expansive forward deck with a large fish box, anchor locker and a convertible cooler seat. Saltwater and freshwater anglers alike will appreciate the ample workspace, six standard rod holders and optional aft livewell. The 210 also offers unprecedented comfort for family cruising with an innovative sun lounge and aft seating options. Optional console T-top, ski tow arch and split bow rail allow you to outfit your Montauk to suit all your boating needs.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Yamaha AR 230 is a sporty boat that stands out from many similar bowriders with her twin Yamaha High Output water jets with the innovative Advanced Responsive handling package, instead of a more typical single stern drive. This bowrider has good water access from her swim platform, and an extra degree of safety due to a lack of exposed propellers that project from the transom. The cockpit has a large wraparound lounge for a very social layout, and plenty of room for passengers to enjoy a fun day on the water. A walkthrough center door provides access to extra seating at the bow. The AR240 High Output is engineered on a longer platform with a higher freeboard to create the most spacious watersports-ready boat in its class.

The Sea Ray SLX 350 delivers in every sense. Yacht Certified and a standard wet bar with refrigerator make entertaining a must. An array of Sea Ray's Next Wave™ innovations-from the noise-quashing powers of Quiet Ride™ to the precision and stability of Dynamic Running Surface to the agility of Axius® joystick technology-take the experience to the next level. VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription:
This 2001 Boston Whaler 26 Conquest is a proven fishing machine! This is a one owner boat, and it really shows! The owner has decided to upgrade to a lager Whaler, and says this one must go! It has every option you would want for Southern California, and Baja fishing. Outriggers, Radar, extra bait tank as well as factory livewell, fish boxes, cooler with seat, bait cutting tray and upgraded Simrad Electronics with side scanner and down vision. 

It's powered by twin Mercury 200hp Optimax Outboards. New power heads installed on both engines only 200 hours ago by a Mercury Dealer in San Diego. Fully maintained and professionally detailed bi-weekly. The owners have taken great care of this boat, and have full records on hand.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Boston Whaler 26 Conquest features a reliable Accutrack hull that provides a stable, dry ride. The deep-V entry smoothes chop while the large fuel capacity allows for all-day cruising. Plenty of interior cabin space makes spending the night comfortable, and the raised-deck cabin affords spacious interiors with ample headroom. Unibond, all-fiberglass construction makes this boat virtually unsinkable. Not only a cruiser, the 26 Conquest is also a fully equipped fishing machine. Amenities include insulated in-deck fish storage, rod racks, gunnel-mounted rod holders, a hardtop with rocket launchers, a bow pulpit, and a livewell. Stern seats fold flat for more fishing room, and a transom door allows for easy fish hauling right into the cockpit. Other standard features include stainless steel grab rails, nonskid surfaces, stainless steel hardware, and marine-grade vinyl upholstery.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: The Boston Whaler Outrage series is the absolute best riding, most solid fishing machine on the planet! Rigged specifically for Southern California and Baja waters, this 2014 Boston Whaler 280 Outrage is a fish ready as it gets. If you're looking for a saltwater fishing boat, then you really need to take a look at this one before you make up your mind. It has twin 250 4-stroke Mercury Verados, Raymarine HD Radar, Auto Pilot, Dual Screen Chart Plotters, with downvision and fishfinder, Competition TACO Outriggers, and low hours. This boat is also equipped with the fishing package, livewell, sink, marine head, and stainless steel anchor with electric windlass!!!

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The 280 Outrage is a superior fishing, entertaining and cruising vessel. Other boat manufacturers can't come close to matching the premium craftsmanship of the 280 Outrage, starting with the boat's state-of-the-art center console. It features a tempered-glass windshield with power-actuated vent, cutting-edge Mercury SmartCraft instrumentation and Raymarine displays, and a heavy-duty integrated hard-top system with floodlights and life jacket storage. An enclosed head lends comfort, and the boat's wide beam and plush seating enhance group pleasure cruises. The 280 Outrage is a bona fide sport fishing machine, too, with serious angling features such as the deluxe leaning post with bait prep area, a 40-gallon livewell, and three massive fishboxes. For those looking for a dedicated tender for their luxury yacht, the 280 Outrage answers the call. Better than a RIB, more than a dinghy, this boat serves as a tender and a memory-making platform for fishing runs and family cruises.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique G21, PCM ZR4 MPI 6.0L, Battery maintenance system, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Mooring cover, Tower speaker prep kit, Tower speakers - 1 pair 7.7 JL M Series speakers, Fresh water engine flush system, Surf select with surf switch, Bow armrests, GoPro quick mounts, Bow arm rests, Heater defroster, Platform cover, Phender pro, Walk-thru air-dam slide in door.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G21 hull design works in concert with the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) to fine-tune the hull under any condition for every application along with 2,850 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast. Sharing the technology and ballast of the entire G-series line, the G21 leaves nothing to be desired in a twenty-one foot boat that maintains the ability to create the most progressive wake and wave in the industry. The Nautique Surf System is seamlessly integrated into the hull offering full wave customization with the ability to transfer to either side in seconds.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique and JL Audio seek to enhance your experience on the water with the ultimate sound system. For 2017, the Super Air Nautique G21 comes standard with the M-Series Elite package including 6 JL speakers and a 10” subwoofer powered by an 8-channel amplifier. If you’re looking to amp it up even more, upgrade to our M-Series Studio Elite package that includes an additional subwoofer with a monoblock amplifier and two in-dash tweeters.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Performance
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G21 customizes each wake and wave setting with enhanced versatility in twenty-one feet of uncompromised G-series performance. Technology and design optimize drivability under every running condition for sports sedan inspired handling unmatched in its class.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf System®
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
The Nautique Surf System® (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

 

https://suncountrymarine.com/top-50-products-nautique-surf-select-wavefront/?home=true&v=7516fd43adaa

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf Select
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine-tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Warranty
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
A Reputation Built On Quality And Integrity

For over 92 years Nautique has built a reputation on the quality of our products and the integrity of our word. True value is created in each precious moment you spend on the water in our boats and we want to ensure you have the best ownership experience possible. When you join the Nautique family, you can rest easy knowing that we take care of our own backing your boat with the Nautique 5-Year Transferable Warranty*

*Nautique warrants to the original user or purchaser, whichever comes first, that each new Nautique boat, as originally manufactured by Nautique, shall under normal authorized use be free of defect in material and workmanship for a period of five (5) years or 500hrs from the date of delivery (whichever comes first). This warranty applies to factory installed components including boat parts, options or other components not manufactured by Nautique Boat Company.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: 2018 AND BEYOND...
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: At Nautique, we are focused on innovation and strive to be constantly improving our product line. We take pride in incorporating state-of-the-art technology and bringing more convenience with new and exciting features each year. We strive to deliver an unmatched experience so that our customers know, there is nothing like stepping onto a new Nautique.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: INTEGRATED STEERING ASSIST™
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The brand-new Integrated Steering Assist utilizes a thruster at the stern of our G-Series models for better maneuverability in tight quarters, around the dock or on the open lake. Quickly move the transom of the boat to the left or right, this functionality greatly improves the driving experience.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: TRANSOM MOUNT
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Want the best angle in the game? Connect your GoPro quickly and easily with our transom GoPro mount so that you can get the perfect photo or video clip.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: JL AUDIO HEAD UNIT AND TRANSOM REMOTE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Our stereo system is even more seamless. Now, control all of the beautifully crisp sound of the JL Audio speakers with the JL Audio MM100s head unit and separate rear transom remote control for unmatched sound quality.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: FULL COLOR INTERIOR
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: A beautifully simple and bold look can take the interior of your new Nautique to the next level. Now, primary interior and seat-boxing choices utilize our entire vinyl collection with a wider array of color options for you to choose from.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: GELCOAT AND VINYL COLORS
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: All-new gel coat color options available for 2018 including Admiral Blue, Solar Red, Admiral Blue Metal Flake, Masters Blue Metal Flake, Victory Red Metal Flake and Medallion Metal Flake. Sahara Sand, Admiral Blue and Solar Red are the new vinyl options.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: ENHANCED COURTESY LIGHTING PACKAGE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Our courtesy lighting package for 2018 now offers a wide variety of LED color options for cup holders, select Nautique badging and courtesy lights throughout the interior of the boat. Completely customize your lighting experience easily via the LINC Panoray Touchscreen.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE STRAPLESS BOARD RACKS
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The all-new over-molded design now provides even more protection for your boards from dents and dings, and still provide the ease-of-use and functionality you know from the best board racks on the market.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: G-SERIES FLIGHT CONTROL TOWER
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Our re-designed towers for this year offer 6” of additional height for improved headroom. New styling and design package color breaks add to the already legendary design and the functionality of the G-Series towers.

.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: GoPro READY
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Connect and control your GoPro camera with our intuitive LINC Panoray touchscreen. You can utilize all of the most-used functions of your GoPro and have a live view of exactly what you’re recording.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: STEREO ZONE CONTROL
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Customize the music volume in different areas of your Nautique with integrated zone control. The ability to customize zones comes standard on all Super Air Nautiques, or you can opt for additional zones for more control and a better experience for your passengers

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: GREATNESS COMES FROM WITHIN
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G23 leaves nothing to be desired as rapid progression follows in its wakes leaving all others behind. An era defined by challenging our imagination is here and with nothing left to prove, we stand alone to compete only with ourselves. Refinement throughout a boat that has achieved the pinnacle of greatness comes together as performance, technology and style become an art form.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: PERFORMANCE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G23 has made the most significant impact on wake-sports in the past decade with superior drivability and a decorated wake and wave that have been honored winning 4X wakeboard and 3X wakesurf boat of the year. Created to perform for all-levels, the Super Air Nautique G-series was built on a dream that has come true.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique Surf System® (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: SOUND
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique and JL Audio have created the best audio systems in the industry with engineered sound that is unmatched on the water. The M-Series Elite package comes standard on the Super Air Nautique G23 featuring 6-JL M-Series speakers and a 10” subwoofer powered by an 8-channel amplifier. Our optional M-Series Studio Elite package steps up for 2017 with two 12” subwoofers and includes the G23 and G25 exclusive JL WaveFront™ technology featuring JL 6.5” M-Series speakers firing through a specially-tuned aperture at the base of the windshield. This premium sound package also features zone control to configure sound throughout your boat just the way you like it.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: ENGINE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G23 comes standard with industry-leading direct-injection from PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology in our H6DI engine. For even more power, supercharge your ride with the XR7 and XS7 engine options. Our 2.0:1 transmission comes standard on all G-series models delivering smooth operation matched with the perfect combination of horsepower and torque.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: HULL
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G-Series hull design has revolutionized the industry proving that it is possible to optimize wake and wave shape for all skill levels and line lengths. Wakeboarders from beginner to pro look to the legendary wake and wave of our G-series boats when pushing themselves and the sport to new levels. Our Nautique Configurable Running Surface (NCRS) is seamlessly integrated to fine-tune the hull under every condition along with 2,850 pounds of sub-floor ballast to customize the experience for every rider. The Nautique Surf System is designed into the hull to work in concert with hull features and the NCRS to create a fully adjustable, perfectly shaped wave on either side of the boat in seconds.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine-tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

For over 92 years Nautique has built a reputation on the quality of our products and the integrity of our word. True value is created in each precious moment you spend on the water in our boats and we want to ensure you have the best ownership experience possible. When you join the Nautique family, you can rest easy knowing that we take care of our own backing your boat with the Nautique 5-Year Transferable Warranty*

NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: SOUND
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique and JL Audio have created the best audio systems in the industry with engineered sound that is unmatched on the water. The M-Series Elite package comes standard on the Super Air Nautique G23 featuring 6-JL M-Series speakers and a 10” subwoofer powered by an 8-channel amplifier. Our optional M-Series Studio Elite package steps up for 2017 with two 12” subwoofers and includes the G23 and G25 exclusive JL WaveFront™ technology featuring JL 6.5” M-Series speakers firing through a specially-tuned aperture at the base of the windshield. This premium sound package also features zone control to configure sound throughout your boat just the way you like it.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: ENGINE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G23 comes standard with industry-leading direct-injection from PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology in our H6DI engine. For even more power, supercharge your ride with the XR7 and XS7 engine options. Our 2.0:1 transmission comes standard on all G-series models delivering smooth operation matched with the perfect combination of horsepower and torque.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: HULL
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G-Series hull design has revolutionized the industry proving that it is possible to optimize wake and wave shape for all skill levels and line lengths. Wakeboarders from beginner to pro look to the legendary wake and wave of our G-series boats when pushing themselves and the sport to new levels. Our Nautique Configurable Running Surface (NCRS) is seamlessly integrated to fine-tune the hull under every condition along with 2,850 pounds of sub-floor ballast to customize the experience for every rider. The Nautique Surf System is designed into the hull to work in concert with hull features and the NCRS to create a fully adjustable, perfectly shaped wave on either side of the boat in seconds.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine-tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:

True value is created in each precious moment you spend on the water in our boats and we want to ensure you have the best ownership experience possible. When you join the Nautique family, you can rest easy knowing that we take care of our own backing your boat with the Nautique 5-Year Transferable Warranty*

*Nautique warrants to the original user or purchaser, whichever comes first, that each new Nautique boat, as originally manufactured by Nautique, shall under normal authorized use be free of defect in material and workmanship for a period of five (5) years or 500hrs from the date of delivery (whichever comes first). VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique G23, Powered by H6 Direct Injection 6.2l, Tungsten grey interior deck color, 2 pair of 8.8 JL M-Series speakers, Tower mounted surf pockets, Mystic White hull color, Freshwater engine flush system, GoPro ready quick mount with dual transom attachments, LINC panoray, Surf select with surf switch system, Ultra premium steering wheel in hand stitched leather, Battery maintenance system, Boat mate trailer, Full boat cover, Platform cover.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: 2018 AND BEYOND...
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: At Nautique, we are focused on innovation and strive to be constantly improving our product line. We take pride in incorporating state-of-the-art technology and bringing more convenience with new and exciting features each year. We strive to deliver an unmatched experience so that our customers know, there is nothing like stepping onto a new Nautique.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: INTEGRATED STEERING ASSIST™
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The brand-new Integrated Steering Assist utilizes a thruster at the stern of our G-Series models for better maneuverability in tight quarters, around the dock or on the open lake. Quickly move the transom of the boat to the left or right, this functionality greatly improves the driving experience.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: TRANSOM MOUNT
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Want the best angle in the game? Connect your GoPro quickly and easily with our transom GoPro mount so that you can get the perfect photo or video clip.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: JL AUDIO HEAD UNIT AND TRANSOM REMOTE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Our stereo system is even more seamless. Now, control all of the beautifully crisp sound of the JL Audio speakers with the JL Audio MM100s head unit and separate rear transom remote control for unmatched sound quality.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: FULL COLOR INTERIOR
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: A beautifully simple and bold look can take the interior of your new Nautique to the next level. Now, primary interior and seat-boxing choices utilize our entire vinyl collection with a wider array of color options for you to choose from.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: GELCOAT AND VINYL COLORS
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: All-new gel coat color options available for 2018 including Admiral Blue, Solar Red, Admiral Blue Metal Flake, Masters Blue Metal Flake, Victory Red Metal Flake and Medallion Metal Flake. Sahara Sand, Admiral Blue and Solar Red are the new vinyl options.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: ENHANCED COURTESY LIGHTING PACKAGE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Our courtesy lighting package for 2018 now offers a wide variety of LED color options for cup holders, select Nautique badging and courtesy lights throughout the interior of the boat. Completely customize your lighting experience easily via the LINC Panoray Touchscreen.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE STRAPLESS BOARD RACKS
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The all-new over-molded design now provides even more protection for your boards from dents and dings, and still provide the ease-of-use and functionality you know from the best board racks on the market.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: G-SERIES FLIGHT CONTROL TOWER
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Our re-designed towers for this year offer 6” of additional height for improved headroom. New styling and design package color breaks add to the already legendary design and the functionality of the G-Series towers.

.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Connect and control your GoPro camera with our intuitive LINC Panoray touchscreen. You can utilize all of the most-used functions of your GoPro and have a live view of exactly what you’re recording.

Refinement throughout a boat that has achieved the pinnacle of greatness comes together as performance, technology and style become an art form.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: PERFORMANCE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G23 has made the most significant impact on wake-sports in the past decade with superior drivability and a decorated wake and wave that have been honored winning 4X wakeboard and 3X wakesurf boat of the year. Created to perform for all-levels, the Super Air Nautique G-series was built on a dream that has come true.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique Surf System® (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: SOUND
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique and JL Audio have created the best audio systems in the industry with engineered sound that is unmatched on the water. The M-Series Elite package comes standard on the Super Air Nautique G23 featuring 6-JL M-Series speakers and a 10” subwoofer powered by an 8-channel amplifier. Our optional M-Series Studio Elite package steps up for 2017 with two 12” subwoofers and includes the G23 and G25 exclusive JL WaveFront™ technology featuring JL 6.5” M-Series speakers firing through a specially-tuned aperture at the base of the windshield. This premium sound package also features zone control to configure sound throughout your boat just the way you like it.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: ENGINE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G23 comes standard with industry-leading direct-injection from PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology in our H6DI engine. For even more power, supercharge your ride with the XR7 and XS7 engine options. Our 2.0:1 transmission comes standard on all G-series models delivering smooth operation matched with the perfect combination of horsepower and torque.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: HULL
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G-Series hull design has revolutionized the industry proving that it is possible to optimize wake and wave shape for all skill levels and line lengths. Wakeboarders from beginner to pro look to the legendary wake and wave of our G-series boats when pushing themselves and the sport to new levels. Our Nautique Configurable Running Surface (NCRS) is seamlessly integrated to fine-tune the hull under every condition along with 2,850 pounds of sub-floor ballast to customize the experience for every rider. The Nautique Surf System is designed into the hull to work in concert with hull features and the NCRS to create a fully adjustable, perfectly shaped wave on either side of the boat in seconds.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine-tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:

True value is created in each precious moment you spend on the water in our boats and we want to ensure you have the best ownership experience possible.
