VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique G23, PCM H6 6.2L, Enhanced courtesy lighting package (Customized colors on illuminated cupholders, courtesy lights, and interior chromax badging), M Series Studio Elite stereo, In-floor cooler, Transom cooler, Flip-up lounger seat, Nautique awareness camera, GoPro ready rotating tow point, NCRS Nautique Configurable Running Surface with Hydro-gate, Nautique Panoray with Helm Control, Zero Off GPS speed control, NSS Nautique Surf Select with WAVEPLATE, Wake package with factory 2,850 lbs. ballast system, Nautique strapless board racks, Surf pipe exhaust, Power management with Dual batteries, Navigation and docking light array, LED courtesy lights, Walk-thru ari-damn pocket door, Bimini tower with surf pockets, Bow armrests, Bow filler cushion, Design package, Freshwater engine flush, Towable/Mooring cover, Platform cover, Ultra premium steering wheel, Tandem axle trailer.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: 2018 AND BEYOND...
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: At Nautique, we are focused on innovation and strive to be constantly improving our product line. We take pride in incorporating state-of-the-art technology and bringing more convenience with new and exciting features each year. We strive to deliver an unmatched experience so that our customers know, there is nothing like stepping onto a new Nautique.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: INTEGRATED STEERING ASSIST™
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The brand-new Integrated Steering Assist utilizes a thruster at the stern of our G-Series models for better maneuverability in tight quarters, around the dock or on the open lake. Quickly move the transom of the boat to the left or right, this functionality greatly improves the driving experience.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: TRANSOM MOUNT
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Want the best angle in the game? Connect your GoPro quickly and easily with our transom GoPro mount so that you can get the perfect photo or video clip.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: JL AUDIO HEAD UNIT AND TRANSOM REMOTE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Our stereo system is even more seamless. Now, control all of the beautifully crisp sound of the JL Audio speakers with the JL Audio MM100s head unit and separate rear transom remote control for unmatched sound quality.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: FULL COLOR INTERIOR
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: A beautifully simple and bold look can take the interior of your new Nautique to the next level. Now, primary interior and seat-boxing choices utilize our entire vinyl collection with a wider array of color options for you to choose from.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: GELCOAT AND VINYL COLORS
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: All-new gel coat color options available for 2018 including Admiral Blue, Solar Red, Admiral Blue Metal Flake, Masters Blue Metal Flake, Victory Red Metal Flake and Medallion Metal Flake. Sahara Sand, Admiral Blue and Solar Red are the new vinyl options.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: ENHANCED COURTESY LIGHTING PACKAGE
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Our courtesy lighting package for 2018 now offers a wide variety of LED color options for cup holders, select Nautique badging and courtesy lights throughout the interior of the boat. Completely customize your lighting experience easily via the LINC Panoray Touchscreen.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: NAUTIQUE STRAPLESS BOARD RACKS
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The all-new over-molded design now provides even more protection for your boards from dents and dings, and still provide the ease-of-use and functionality you know from the best board racks on the market.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: G-SERIES FLIGHT CONTROL TOWER
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Our re-designed towers for this year offer 6” of additional height for improved headroom. New styling and design package color breaks add to the already legendary design and the functionality of the G-Series towers.

.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: GoPro READY
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Connect and control your GoPro camera with our intuitive LINC Panoray touchscreen. You can utilize all of the most-used functions of your GoPro and have a live view of exactly what you’re recording.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: STEREO ZONE CONTROL
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Customize the music volume in different areas of your Nautique with integrated zone control. The ability to customize zones comes standard on all Super Air Nautiques, or you can opt for additional zones for more control and a better experience for your passengers

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique GS20, PCM H5 Direct Injected 5.3L, MX Series stereo, Nautique Configurable Running Surface (NCRS) with Hydro-plate, Nautique LINC PANORAY with helm control Zero Off GPS, Wake package (NSS, WAVEPLATE, 1850 Integrated ballast), Flight control tower with rotating wakeboard/wakesurf racks, Navigation and docking light array, Cleats (4), LED courtesy lights, Cooler (removable), Waste receptacle, Surf pipe, Walk-thru air-dam door (slide-in), Nautique awareness cam, Battery maintenance system 110, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Bow filler cushion, Freshwater engine flush, Towable mooring cover, Platform cover, 1 Pair 7.7 JL M-series tower speakers, Surf Select with surf switch, Tandem axle trailer.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
The GS20 blends masterful, award-winning designs from both the undisputed industry-leading G-Series and the world-record setting Ski Nautique Series into the ultimate 20-foot boat that’s sure to be a crowd pleaser for everyone. Loaded with new features, this boat has it all and then some! From the 12.4” Nautique LINC Panoray touchscreen and optional Nautique Awareness camera, to a new-age dash design and convenient transom seating, functionality and style meet ultimate versatility in 20 feet of perfection.

When you want to escape the confines of discipline-specific performance, the focus must not be on what you can’t have but on what you can. Viewing versatility as its own specialty, the Super Air Nautique GS20 transforms from a ski boat to a wake boat to a surf boat in a way that steps into a new realm of engineering, design and technology.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS20 is the first of its kind with a hull designed to optimize the wake and wave under running conditions for wakeboarding, wakesurfing, and waterskiing. Distinct characteristics taken from our world-record breaking Ski Nautique 200 begin at the bow transforming into features of our award-winning G-series at the transom. New technology in the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) has been developed for flawless performance at every speed and user setting. Select the Slalom Ski profile with NCRS Ski Assist to hit the course and fill 1,850 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast with Wake and Surf settings when you’re ready to go big.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Surf System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique Surf System with Waveplate® comes standard on the Super Air Nautique GS20 giving the world’s most versatile towboat a world-class wave on demand. Integrating the Nautique Surf System into hull features inspired by our latest G-series, we are able to maximize wave size and push along with the ability to customize wave shape and initiate transfers at the touch of a button on the LINC PANORAY screen.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique brings you superior sound in the ultimate package by way of JL Audio components delivering the best sound systems in the industry. Rock your boat with 4 MX-series speakers standard on the Super Air Nautique GS20 or turn it up with the MX-Series Premier package featuring two additional speakers in the bow and a 10” subwoofer powered by a JL M600/6 amplifier. Keep it cranking behind the boat with the optional 7.7” or 8.8” JL M-Series tower speakers.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique G25, XR7 Supercharged MPI 6.2L, Walk-thru air dam door, Battery maintenance system, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Retractable bow arm rests, Bow filler cushion, Freshwater engine flush system, Enhanced courtesy light package, Towable/Mooring cover, LINC Panoray Navionics Map, Platform cover, Two pair of JL audio 8.8 tower speakers, Ultra premium steering wheel in hand stitched leather, M Series studio elite stereo with Wavefront technology, Surf select with surf switch, Triple axle trailer.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Interior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Stepping into a Super Air Nautique G25 is an experience that puts luxury, comfort, and space beyond comprehension. We have moved into a new realm of design for 2017 with a unique, open helm that puts abstract form into perfect function. The all-new 12.4” LINC PANORAY touchscreen puts intuitive control at your fingertips along with menu customization in our new switchboard feature. All-new colors give your G25 interior a unique style with seating for nineteen so bring your family, bring your friends, and enjoy the ride of a lifetime.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Exterior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Exude power with exquisite styling on a grand scale in the Super Air Nautique G25. For 2017, our G-series flight control tower features all-new styling that emphasizes aggression with strength and functionality. Stay unique with our new white chromax and gel coat color options to deliver more customization to our largest canvas. Add our Galaxy or new Surf graphics and stand out like no one else on the water.

Built on a dream that brings everyone along, experiences on the water only get better when shared. Large waterways are open for endless adventure so grab everyone, get in, and GO!

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: GS22
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
EMBARK ON AN ADVENTURE WITHOUT LIMITS

The newest addition to a family that knows no limits is here! The Super Air Nautique GS22 expands on the idea of uncompromised versatility realized in an all-new series of boats ready for adventure. Embark on a journey with endless possibilities in twenty-two feet tailor-made for absolutely everything.

Born out of award-winning, record-breaking lineage the Super Air Nautique GS-Series delivers where others fall short. See the next evolution in ideal execution with a perfect match that finally answers the multi-sport demand in style. The dream of combining the Ski Nautique and G-Series is a reality ready to be experienced, because you’ll never believe you can have it all…until you do.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Interior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The GS-Series interior design is revolutionary in functionality and use of space. Twenty-two feet feels endless in the Super Air Nautique GS22 with a progressive flow of innovative features and plush comfort. Configurable rear-facing seating options keep your eyes on the action with our standard port side flip-up lounge seat and starboard removable backrest. Large communicating storage ensures you have a place for everything in a boat that can do it all. The all-new 12.4” LINC PANORAY touchscreen display highlights the helm giving you more intuitive control of each feature than ever before. Access your favorite functions in an instant with the new customizable Switchboard feature and never lose sight of your surroundings with the all-new optional Nautique Awareness camera.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Exterior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS22 is visual inspiration that tells the story of all-encompassing capability from bow to stern. Functional style is beautifully executed with extruded hull features that give the GS22 a powerful presence on the water. Customize your masterpiece with an array of vibrant colors and the option of our Galaxy or Surf graphic for a look that keeps all eyes on you.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Performance
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Enter a new world of possibility with a breakthrough in multi-sport performance in the all-new Super Air Nautique GS22. Combining characteristics from our award-winning G-Series and record-breaking Ski Nautique, the all-new GS-Series is specialized versatility unlike anything that has come before. The ability to transform from a ski boat to a wake boat to a surf boat has been achieved through progressive engineering and new technology specifically applied to perform for every activity exceptionally well.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: In a boat with endless possibilities, turn it up inside your Nautique as much as you do behind it with our premium JL Audio sound systems. Equip your Super Air Nautique GS22 with four MX-Series speakers in our standard system or turn it up with the MX-Series Premier package featuring two additional speakers in the bow and a 10” subwoofer powered by a JL M600/6 amplifier. Keep it cranking behind the boat with the optional 7.7” or 8.8” JL M-Series tower speakers.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Engine
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS22 comes standard with the proven power of the PCM ZR4 engine. Upgrade to the groundbreaking PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology H5DI and H6DI direct-inject engines and experience industry-leading precision, power, and torque that have taken towed watersports by storm.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS-Series hull design is the first of its kind optimizing the wake and wave under running conditions for wakeboarding, wakesurfing, and waterskiing. Distinct characteristics taken from our world-record breaking Ski Nautique begin at the bow transforming into features of our award-winning G-Series at the transom. New technology in the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) has been developed for flawless performance at every speed and user setting. Select the Slalom Ski profile with NCRS Ski Assist to hit the course and fill 2,250 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast in the GS22 with Wake and Surf settings when you’re ready to go big.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM (NSS)

The Nautique Surf System (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.


NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT

Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique G21, PCM ZR4 MPI 6.0L, Enhanced courtesy lighting package, Stereo M Series Elite, Mystic white hull color, Tungsten grey seat accents, Flip up lounge seat, Nautique awareness camera, GoPro ready rotating tow point, Nautique Configurable Running Surface, Nautique LINC PANORAY with helm control and zero off GPS control, Flight Control Tower with Nautique strapless board racks, Surf pipe exhaust, Navigation and Docking light array, Design package, Battery maintenance system, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Mooring cover, Tower speaker prep kit, Tower speakers - 1 pair 7.7 JL M Series speakers, Fresh water engine flush system, Surf select with surf switch, Bow armrests, GoPro quick mounts, Bow arm rests, platform cover, Walk-thru air-dam slide in door.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G21 hull design works in concert with the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) to fine-tune the hull under any condition for every application along with 2,850 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast. Sharing the technology and ballast of the entire G-series line, the G21 leaves nothing to be desired in a twenty-one foot boat that maintains the ability to create the most progressive wake and wave in the industry. The Nautique Surf System is seamlessly integrated into the hull offering full wave customization with the ability to transfer to either side in seconds.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique and JL Audio seek to enhance your experience on the water with the ultimate sound system. For 2017, the Super Air Nautique G21 comes standard with the M-Series Elite package including 6 JL speakers and a 10” subwoofer powered by an 8-channel amplifier. If you’re looking to amp it up even more, upgrade to our M-Series Studio Elite package that includes an additional subwoofer with a monoblock amplifier and two in-dash tweeters.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Performance
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G21 customizes each wake and wave setting with enhanced versatility in twenty-one feet of uncompromised G-series performance. AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: 230 Outrage
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The bold 230 Outrage delivers huge fishing capability and huge comfort to match. The spacious bow area features ample seating and convenient in-floor and under-seat storage. Meanwhile, the roomy cockpit features the Converting Leaning Post, which conceals a handy work station and extra aft-facing seating. Available with an integrated fiberglass hardtop, premium navigation and fish-finding technology, JL Audio speakers and more, the 230 Outrage rises to any occasion.

Embark on a journey with endless possibilities in twenty-two feet tailor-made for absolutely everything.

Born out of award-winning, record-breaking lineage the Super Air Nautique GS-Series delivers where others fall short. See the next evolution in ideal execution with a perfect match that finally answers the multi-sport demand in style. The dream of combining the Ski Nautique and G-Series is a reality ready to be experienced, because you’ll never believe you can have it all…until you do.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Interior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The GS-Series interior design is revolutionary in functionality and use of space. Twenty-two feet feels endless in the Super Air Nautique GS22 with a progressive flow of innovative features and plush comfort. Configurable rear-facing seating options keep your eyes on the action with our standard port side flip-up lounge seat and starboard removable backrest. Large communicating storage ensures you have a place for everything in a boat that can do it all. The all-new 12.4” LINC PANORAY touchscreen display highlights the helm giving you more intuitive control of each feature than ever before. Access your favorite functions in an instant with the new customizable Switchboard feature and never lose sight of your surroundings with the all-new optional Nautique Awareness camera.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Exterior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS22 is visual inspiration that tells the story of all-encompassing capability from bow to stern. Functional style is beautifully executed with extruded hull features that give the GS22 a powerful presence on the water. Customize your masterpiece with an array of vibrant colors and the option of our Galaxy or Surf graphic for a look that keeps all eyes on you.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Performance
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Enter a new world of possibility with a breakthrough in multi-sport performance in the all-new Super Air Nautique GS22. Combining characteristics from our award-winning G-Series and record-breaking Ski Nautique, the all-new GS-Series is specialized versatility unlike anything that has come before. The ability to transform from a ski boat to a wake boat to a surf boat has been achieved through progressive engineering and new technology specifically applied to perform for every activity exceptionally well.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: In a boat with endless possibilities, turn it up inside your Nautique as much as you do behind it with our premium JL Audio sound systems. Equip your Super Air Nautique GS22 with four MX-Series speakers in our standard system or turn it up with the MX-Series Premier package featuring two additional speakers in the bow and a 10” subwoofer powered by a JL M600/6 amplifier. Keep it cranking behind the boat with the optional 7.7” or 8.8” JL M-Series tower speakers.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Engine
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS22 comes standard with the proven power of the PCM ZR4 engine. Upgrade to the groundbreaking PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology H5DI and H6DI direct-inject engines and experience industry-leading precision, power, and torque that have taken towed watersports by storm.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS-Series hull design is the first of its kind optimizing the wake and wave under running conditions for wakeboarding, wakesurfing, and waterskiing. Distinct characteristics taken from our world-record breaking Ski Nautique begin at the bow transforming into features of our award-winning G-Series at the transom. New technology in the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) has been developed for flawless performance at every speed and user setting. Select the Slalom Ski profile with NCRS Ski Assist to hit the course and fill 2,250 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast in the GS22 with Wake and Surf settings when you’re ready to go big.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM (NSS)

The Nautique Surf System (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.


NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT

Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: The Nautique GS24
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Brand-new for 2018, the Super Air Nautique GS24 is a multi-sport boat that takes the versatility of the GS-Series to the next level. Like its smaller siblings, the GS20 and GS22, the GS24 has acquired hull characteristics from our award-winning G-Series and Ski Nautique 200 models to produce the largest, most capable multi-sport boat in the industry.

With all 24-feet of innovative technology it doesn’t leave anything to be desired; and even better, you won’t leave any of your friends or family on the dock. Incorporating all the amenities you expect out of a Super Air Nautique with generous room throughout, the GS24 is ready to give you and your family the best summer ever whether surfing, riding or skiing.

 

PERFORMANCE

In the past, multi-sport performance has always left something to be desired. Now, with the Super Air Nautique GS24, you have the ability to wakesurf, wakeboard or waterski at very high levels without compromise. Never before could you transition from sport to sport so proficiently until the debut of the GS-Series; and with two more feet of room, you can invite more people to experience the versatility. This all-new model has taken the multi-sport boat into a whole new realm, and with room for everyone the GS24 is a true crowd pleaser.

SOUND

For the 2018 model year, the Super Air Nautique GS24 is boasting a brand-new JL Audio MM100s head unit that delivers crisp, clear sound into the JL Audio speakers. This boat comes standard with the MX-Series Studio Premier package, which includes 6 JL Audio speakers throughout the boat, customizable zone control, a 10” JL Audio subwoofer and a 6-channel JL Audio amplifier. Add 7.7 or 8.8 JL M-Series tower speakers to enjoy tunes behind the boat, too.

ENGINE

The Super Air Nautique GS24 comes standard with the proven power of the PCM ZR4 engine. Upgrade to the groundbreaking PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology H5DI and H6DI direct-inject engines and experience industry-leading precision, power, and torque. If that isn’t enough, the Supercharged XR7 workhorse will provide more power, torque and precision than any other marine engine in the towboat market.

HULL

The Super Air Nautique GS24 hull truly optimizes the way the wake is formed so that you can wakesurf, wakeboard or waterski. It has taken distinct hull characteristics from our world-record breaking Ski Nautique at the bow, as well as features of our award-winning G-Series at the transom. New technology in the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) has been developed for flawless performance at any speed for any activity. Select the Slalom Ski profile with NCRS Ski Assist, or quickly fill the 2,500 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast and you are on the way to surf or wakeboard..

NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM (NSS)

The Nautique Surf System (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is seamlessly integrated into the hull of the brand-new GS24. Engaging on either side of the transom at surf speeds, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be completely customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to switch up ballast or people and fine tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT

Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat. Gone are the days of yelling and hand signaling to the driver so you can perfectly time your wave transfers, with the Nautique Surf Switch, you can easily change what side of the boat your surf wave is on at the touch of a button. A handheld controller you can connect to your wrist, Surf Switch puts you in complete control so you can work on your frontside and backside game whenever your heart desires.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Super Air Nautique 210, PCM ZR4 MPI, Nautique Configurable Running Surface with automated Hydro-Gate, waste receptacle, Nautique Surf System with WAVEPLATE, Wake package with 1150 lbs. of integrated ballast, Flight control tower with rotating wakeboard/wakesurf racks, Surf pipe exhaust, Cooler (removable softside), Zero off GPS, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Towable mooring cover, 1 Pair 7.7 JL tower speakers, Surf Select with Surf Switch, Tandem axle trailer.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique 210 takes a purist’s approach to honoring the continued progression of this trend-setting wake boat. Incorporating new technology and design continues the rise of a legend that has seen us through from the beginning. Igniting a passion for wake-sports that rages beyond what we imagined, every set will remind you that individuality is freedom living on the edge.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Our stereo system from JL Audio never fails to intensify your experience on the water. The Super Air Nautique 210 comes standard with four JL MX-Series speakers. Upgrade to the MX-Series Premier package by adding two more JL MX-Series speakers and a 10” subwoofer to make it complete. Turn it up behind the boat with the choice of our 6x9 RMA/Focal or premium JL M-Series 7.7” tower speakers.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique 210 hull design maintains the performance this legend was built on. The heart and soul of this design remains unchanged while integrating new technology and features that have given us the ability to enhance your experience. The Nautique Surf System is integrated into the hull to work seamlessly in creating a fully customizable surf wave that allows you to transfer to either side in seconds with the boat evenly weighted. Our patented HydroGate™ fine-tunes your ride with the ability to adjust the boat’s attitude on the fly.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Surf System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique Surf System® (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique GS22, PCM ZR4 MPI 6.0L, MX-Series stereo, Removable lean back (starboard), Flip-Up lounge seat, Nautique Configurable Running Surface with Hydro-Plate, Nautique LINC PANORAY with helm control, Zero Off GPS, Wake package with 2250 lbs. of integrated ballast, Nautique Surf System (NSS) with WAVEPLATE, Flight control tower with rotating wakeboard/wakesurf racks, Navigation and docking light array, Surf pipe exhaust, Cleats (4), LED courtesy lighting, Walk-thru air-dam door, Awareness camera, Battery maintenance system, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Bow filler cushion, Towable/Mooring cover, Platform cover, Retractable ski pylon, 1 pair 7.7 JL M-Series tower speakers, Surf Select with surf switch, Tandem axle trailer.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: GS22
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
EMBARK ON AN ADVENTURE WITHOUT LIMITS

The newest addition to a family that knows no limits is here! The Super Air Nautique GS22 expands on the idea of uncompromised versatility realized in an all-new series of boats ready for adventure. Embark on a journey with endless possibilities in twenty-two feet tailor-made for absolutely everything.

Born out of award-winning, record-breaking lineage the Super Air Nautique GS-Series delivers where others fall short. See the next evolution in ideal execution with a perfect match that finally answers the multi-sport demand in style. The dream of combining the Ski Nautique and G-Series is a reality ready to be experienced, because you’ll never believe you can have it all…until you do.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Interior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The GS-Series interior design is revolutionary in functionality and use of space. Twenty-two feet feels endless in the Super Air Nautique GS22 with a progressive flow of innovative features and plush comfort. Configurable rear-facing seating options keep your eyes on the action with our standard port side flip-up lounge seat and starboard removable backrest. Large communicating storage ensures you have a place for everything in a boat that can do it all. The all-new 12.4” LINC PANORAY touchscreen display highlights the helm giving you more intuitive control of each feature than ever before. Access your favorite functions in an instant with the new customizable Switchboard feature and never lose sight of your surroundings with the all-new optional Nautique Awareness camera.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Exterior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS22 is visual inspiration that tells the story of all-encompassing capability from bow to stern. Functional style is beautifully executed with extruded hull features that give the GS22 a powerful presence on the water. Customize your masterpiece with an array of vibrant colors and the option of our Galaxy or Surf graphic for a look that keeps all eyes on you.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Performance
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Enter a new world of possibility with a breakthrough in multi-sport performance in the all-new Super Air Nautique GS22. Combining characteristics from our award-winning G-Series and record-breaking Ski Nautique, the all-new GS-Series is specialized versatility unlike anything that has come before. The ability to transform from a ski boat to a wake boat to a surf boat has been achieved through progressive engineering and new technology specifically applied to perform for every activity exceptionally well.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: In a boat with endless possibilities, turn it up inside your Nautique as much as you do behind it with our premium JL Audio sound systems. Equip your Super Air Nautique GS22 with four MX-Series speakers in our standard system or turn it up with the MX-Series Premier package featuring two additional speakers in the bow and a 10” subwoofer powered by a JL M600/6 amplifier. Keep it cranking behind the boat with the optional 7.7” or 8.8” JL M-Series tower speakers.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Engine
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS22 comes standard with the proven power of the PCM ZR4 engine. Upgrade to the groundbreaking PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology H5DI and H6DI direct-inject engines and experience industry-leading precision, power, and torque that have taken towed watersports by storm.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS-Series hull design is the first of its kind optimizing the wake and wave under running conditions for wakeboarding, wakesurfing, and waterskiing. Distinct characteristics taken from our world-record breaking Ski Nautique begin at the bow transforming into features of our award-winning G-Series at the transom. New technology in the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) has been developed for flawless performance at every speed and user setting. Select the Slalom Ski profile with NCRS Ski Assist to hit the course and fill 2,250 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast in the GS22 with Wake and Surf settings when you’re ready to go big.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM (NSS)

The Nautique Surf System (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.


NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT

Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique GS 24, PCM ZR4 MPI 6.0L, MX-Series Studio Premier stereo with Zone Control, Removable lean back (starboard), Flip-Up lounge seat, Nautique Configurable Running Surface with Hydro-Plate, Nautique LINC PANORAY with helm control, Zero Off GPS, Wake package with 2500 lbs. of integrated ballast, Nautique Surf System (NSS) with WAVEPLATE, Flight control tower with rotating wakeboard/wakesurf racks, Navigation and docking light array, Surf pipe exhaust, Cleats (4), LED courtesy lighting, Walk-thru air-dam door, Awareness camera, Battery maintenance system, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Bow filler cushion, Towable/Mooring cover, Platform cover, Retractable ski pylon, 1 pair 7.7 JL M-Series tower speakers, Surf Select with surf switch, Tandem axle trailer.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: The Nautique GS24
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Brand-new for 2018, the Super Air Nautique GS24 is a multi-sport boat that takes the versatility of the GS-Series to the next level. Like its smaller siblings, the GS20 and GS22, the GS24 has acquired hull characteristics from our award-winning G-Series and Ski Nautique 200 models to produce the largest, most capable multi-sport boat in the industry.

With all 24-feet of innovative technology it doesn’t leave anything to be desired; and even better, you won’t leave any of your friends or family on the dock. Incorporating all the amenities you expect out of a Super Air Nautique with generous room throughout, the GS24 is ready to give you and your family the best summer ever whether surfing, riding or skiing.

 

PERFORMANCE

In the past, multi-sport performance has always left something to be desired. Now, with the Super Air Nautique GS24, you have the ability to wakesurf, wakeboard or waterski at very high levels without compromise. Never before could you transition from sport to sport so proficiently until the debut of the GS-Series; and with two more feet of room, you can invite more people to experience the versatility. This all-new model has taken the multi-sport boat into a whole new realm, and with room for everyone the GS24 is a true crowd pleaser.

SOUND

For the 2018 model year, the Super Air Nautique GS24 is boasting a brand-new JL Audio MM100s head unit that delivers crisp, clear sound into the JL Audio speakers. This boat comes standard with the MX-Series Studio Premier package, which includes 6 JL Audio speakers throughout the boat, customizable zone control, a 10” JL Audio subwoofer and a 6-channel JL Audio amplifier. Add 7.7 or 8.8 JL M-Series tower speakers to enjoy tunes behind the boat, too.

ENGINE

The Super Air Nautique GS24 comes standard with the proven power of the PCM ZR4 engine. Upgrade to the groundbreaking PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology H5DI and H6DI direct-inject engines and experience industry-leading precision, power, and torque. If that isn’t enough, the Supercharged XR7 workhorse will provide more power, torque and precision than any other marine engine in the towboat market.

HULL

The Super Air Nautique GS24 hull truly optimizes the way the wake is formed so that you can wakesurf, wakeboard or waterski. It has taken distinct hull characteristics from our world-record breaking Ski Nautique at the bow, as well as features of our award-winning G-Series at the transom. New technology in the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) has been developed for flawless performance at any speed for any activity. Select the Slalom Ski profile with NCRS Ski Assist, or quickly fill the 2,500 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast and you are on the way to surf or wakeboard..

NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM (NSS)

The Nautique Surf System (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is seamlessly integrated into the hull of the brand-new GS24. Engaging on either side of the transom at surf speeds, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be completely customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to switch up ballast or people and fine tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT

Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat. Gone are the days of yelling and hand signaling to the driver so you can perfectly time your wave transfers, with the Nautique Surf Switch, you can easily change what side of the boat your surf wave is on at the touch of a button. A handheld controller you can connect to your wrist, Surf Switch puts you in complete control so you can work on your frontside and backside game whenever your heart desires.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Steering System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Joystick Control

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: 330 Outrage
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
The all-new 330 Outrage® is an outstanding saltwater performer, built on a foundation of core confidence. Boston Whaler’s precision-engineered design delivers a smooth, dry, comfortable ride—the optimal balance of stability and softness. Handling is beautifully predictable with seamless control, giving you ease and confidence like you’ve never felt before. Fishing features and options galore, including numerous comfort-minded amenities for you and your guests, make the 330 perfect for entertaining and whatever offshore adventures you dream up. Not only is this new Outrage up to the task, but it’s also designed to make every task a pleasure.

  • Private enclosed head compartment in the console features a VacuFlush® toilet, porthole and storage space.
  • Plus forward lounge seat with armrests opens to reveal a cavernous storage compartment.
  • Access protection from midday rays with the optional bow sunshade.
  • Enjoy ample fish-fighting room in the cockpit, courtesy of a wide beam and fold-away aft bench.
  • Smart bow seating, a convenient dive door and optional bow and aft sunshades empower great entertaining.

Estimated arrival in January.

2018 Nautique G21, PCM H6 Direct Injected 6.2L, Enhanced courtesy lighting package, Stereo M Series Elite, Softsided removable cooler, Flip up lounge seat, Nautique awareness camera, GoPro ready rotating tow point, Nautique Configurable Running Surface, Nautique LINC PANORAY with helm control and zero off GPS control, Flight Control Tower with Nautique strapless board racks, Surf pipe exhaust, Navigation and Docking light array, Design package, Tower mounted bimini with surf pockets, Tower speaker prep kit, Tower speakers - 1 pair 8.8 JL M Series speakers, Tower speaker covers, Battery maintenance system, Mooring cover, Platform cover, Fresh water engine flush system, Linc Panoray with river mode paddle, Bow arm rests, Bow filler cushion, M Series Studio Elite, Surf select with surf switch, Ultra premium steering wheel, GoPro quick mounts,  Walk-thru air-dam slide in door.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G21 hull design works in concert with the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) to fine-tune the hull under any condition for every application along with 2,850 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast. Sharing the technology and ballast of the entire G-series line, the G21 leaves nothing to be desired in a twenty-one foot boat that maintains the ability to create the most progressive wake and wave in the industry. The Nautique Surf System is seamlessly integrated into the hull offering full wave customization with the ability to transfer to either side in seconds.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique and JL Audio seek to enhance your experience on the water with the ultimate sound system. For 2017, the Super Air Nautique G21 comes standard with the M-Series Elite package including 6 JL speakers and a 10” subwoofer powered by an 8-channel amplifier. If you’re looking to amp it up even more, upgrade to our M-Series Studio Elite package that includes an additional subwoofer with a monoblock amplifier and two in-dash tweeters.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Performance
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G21 customizes each wake and wave setting with enhanced versatility in twenty-one feet of uncompromised G-series performance. Technology and design optimize drivability under every running condition for sports sedan inspired handling unmatched in its class.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf System®
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
The Nautique Surf System® (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf Select
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine-tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

For over 92 years Nautique has built a reputation on the quality of our products and the integrity of our word. True value is created in each precious moment you spend on the water in our boats and we want to ensure you have the best ownership experience possible. When you join the Nautique family, you can rest easy knowing that we take care of our own backing your boat with the Nautique 5-Year Transferable Warranty*

*Nautique warrants to the original user or purchaser, whichever comes first, that each new Nautique boat, as originally manufactured by Nautique, shall under normal authorized use be free of defect in material and workmanship for a period of five (5) years or 500hrs from the date of delivery (whichever comes first). This warranty applies to factory installed components including boat parts, options or other components not manufactured by Nautique Boat Company.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: GS22
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
EMBARK ON AN ADVENTURE WITHOUT LIMITS

The newest addition to a family that knows no limits is here! The Super Air Nautique GS22 expands on the idea of uncompromised versatility realized in an all-new series of boats ready for adventure. Embark on a journey with endless possibilities in twenty-two feet tailor-made for absolutely everything.

Born out of award-winning, record-breaking lineage the Super Air Nautique GS-Series delivers where others fall short. See the next evolution in ideal execution with a perfect match that finally answers the multi-sport demand in style. The dream of combining the Ski Nautique and G-Series is a reality ready to be experienced, because you’ll never believe you can have it all…until you do.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Interior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The GS-Series interior design is revolutionary in functionality and use of space. Twenty-two feet feels endless in the Super Air Nautique GS22 with a progressive flow of innovative features and plush comfort. Configurable rear-facing seating options keep your eyes on the action with our standard port side flip-up lounge seat and starboard removable backrest. Large communicating storage ensures you have a place for everything in a boat that can do it all. The all-new 12.4” LINC PANORAY touchscreen display highlights the helm giving you more intuitive control of each feature than ever before. Access your favorite functions in an instant with the new customizable Switchboard feature and never lose sight of your surroundings with the all-new optional Nautique Awareness camera.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Exterior
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS22 is visual inspiration that tells the story of all-encompassing capability from bow to stern. Functional style is beautifully executed with extruded hull features that give the GS22 a powerful presence on the water. Customize your masterpiece with an array of vibrant colors and the option of our Galaxy or Surf graphic for a look that keeps all eyes on you.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Performance
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Enter a new world of possibility with a breakthrough in multi-sport performance in the all-new Super Air Nautique GS22. Combining characteristics from our award-winning G-Series and record-breaking Ski Nautique, the all-new GS-Series is specialized versatility unlike anything that has come before. The ability to transform from a ski boat to a wake boat to a surf boat has been achieved through progressive engineering and new technology specifically applied to perform for every activity exceptionally well.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: In a boat with endless possibilities, turn it up inside your Nautique as much as you do behind it with our premium JL Audio sound systems. Equip your Super Air Nautique GS22 with four MX-Series speakers in our standard system or turn it up with the MX-Series Premier package featuring two additional speakers in the bow and a 10” subwoofer powered by a JL M600/6 amplifier. Keep it cranking behind the boat with the optional 7.7” or 8.8” JL M-Series tower speakers.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Engine
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS22 comes standard with the proven power of the PCM ZR4 engine. Upgrade to the groundbreaking PCM and GM Marine Engine Technology H5DI and H6DI direct-inject engines and experience industry-leading precision, power, and torque that have taken towed watersports by storm.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS-Series hull design is the first of its kind optimizing the wake and wave under running conditions for wakeboarding, wakesurfing, and waterskiing. Distinct characteristics taken from our world-record breaking Ski Nautique begin at the bow transforming into features of our award-winning G-Series at the transom. New technology in the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) has been developed for flawless performance at every speed and user setting. Select the Slalom Ski profile with NCRS Ski Assist to hit the course and fill 2,250 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast in the GS22 with Wake and Surf settings when you’re ready to go big.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
NAUTIQUE SURF SYSTEM (NSS)

The Nautique Surf System (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.


NAUTIQUE SURF SELECT

Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
The GS20 blends masterful, award-winning designs from both the undisputed industry-leading G-Series and the world-record setting Ski Nautique Series into the ultimate 20-foot boat that’s sure to be a crowd pleaser for everyone. Loaded with new features, this boat has it all and then some! From the 12.4” Nautique LINC Panoray touchscreen and optional Nautique Awareness camera, to a new-age dash design and convenient transom seating, functionality and style meet ultimate versatility in 20 feet of perfection.

When you want to escape the confines of discipline-specific performance, the focus must not be on what you can’t have but on what you can. Viewing versatility as its own specialty, the Super Air Nautique GS20 transforms from a ski boat to a wake boat to a surf boat in a way that steps into a new realm of engineering, design and technology.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS20 is the first of its kind with a hull designed to optimize the wake and wave under running conditions for wakeboarding, wakesurfing, and waterskiing. Distinct characteristics taken from our world-record breaking Ski Nautique 200 begin at the bow transforming into features of our award-winning G-series at the transom. New technology in the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) has been developed for flawless performance at every speed and user setting. Select the Slalom Ski profile with NCRS Ski Assist to hit the course and fill 1,850 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast with Wake and Surf settings when you’re ready to go big.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Surf System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique Surf System with Waveplate® comes standard on the Super Air Nautique GS20 giving the world’s most versatile towboat a world-class wave on demand. Integrating the Nautique Surf System into hull features inspired by our latest G-series, we are able to maximize wave size and push along with the ability to customize wave shape and initiate transfers at the touch of a button on the LINC PANORAY screen.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique brings you superior sound in the ultimate package by way of JL Audio components delivering the best sound systems in the industry. Rock your boat with 4 MX-series speakers standard on the Super Air Nautique GS20 or turn it up with the MX-Series Premier package featuring two additional speakers in the bow and a 10” subwoofer powered by a JL M600/6 amplifier. Keep it cranking behind the boat with the optional 7.7” or 8.8” JL M-Series tower speakers.

For 2017, the Super Air Nautique G21 comes standard with the M-Series Elite package including 6 JL speakers and a 10” subwoofer powered by an 8-channel amplifier. If you’re looking to amp it up even more, upgrade to our M-Series Studio Elite package that includes an additional subwoofer with a monoblock amplifier and two in-dash tweeters.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Performance
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique G21 customizes each wake and wave setting with enhanced versatility in twenty-one feet of uncompromised G-series performance. Technology and design optimize drivability under every running condition for sports sedan inspired handling unmatched in its class.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf System®
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
The Nautique Surf System® (NSS) with WAVEPLATE® technology is integrated into the hull to engage on either side of the transom at surf speeds working seamlessly with the running surface to create a larger wave with each pound of ballast. Offering full adjustability, the WAVEPLATE extends outward and down from the transom to intercept and redirect the flow of water forming a wave that can be customized for every surfer. NSS allows surfers to switch sides instantly without the need to offload ballast or people and fine-tune the wave with variable settings that adjust steepness and shape by controlling exactly how much the WAVEPLATE is engaged.

 

https://suncountrymarine.com/top-50-products-nautique-surf-select-wavefront/?home=true&v=7516fd43adaa

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Nautique Surf Select
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique Surf Select gives surfers the ability to customize their ride from behind the boat at the touch of a button. Transfer on the fly with the Nautique Surf Switch to work on your frontside and backside game with no hesitation. Don’t sweat the details and fine-tune your experience right from your wrist with the Surf Select app for Pebble™ watch. Compatible with all waterproof Pebble™ watches, Surf Select adjusts the Zero-Off Speed Control, NSS, NCRS, stereo track and volume while allowing surfers to transfer the wave instantly or at a three-second countdown. New for 2017 Surf Select also features ballast shift on Pebble Time watches allowing you to find perfect balance.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Warranty
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
A Reputation Built On Quality And Integrity

For over 92 years Nautique has built a reputation on the quality of our products and the integrity of our word. True value is created in each precious moment you spend on the water in our boats and we want to ensure you have the best ownership experience possible. When you join the Nautique family, you can rest easy knowing that we take care of our own backing your boat with the Nautique 5-Year Transferable Warranty*

*Nautique warrants to the original user or purchaser, whichever comes first, that each new Nautique boat, as originally manufactured by Nautique, shall under normal authorized use be free of defect in material and workmanship for a period of five (5) years or 500hrs from the date of delivery (whichever comes first). This warranty applies to factory installed components including boat parts, options or other components not manufactured by Nautique Boat Company.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: 350 Coupe
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Introducing the Sundancer 350 Coupe, an exciting new addition to Sea Ray's most iconic series. With a sleek hardtop and enhanced coupe foredeck seating/lounging zone, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is a brilliant entertaining platform and an inviting place to spend entire days on the water. Premium amenities, state-of-the-art technology and unrivaled performance - with your choice of sterndrive or inboard propulsion - combine to deliver a fully enjoyable cruising experience. Options for customization abound, meaning you can make the Coupe totally your own. And with a sleek, stylish aesthetic that's both gorgeously modern and unmistakably Sea Ray, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is a boat you'll be proud to own and proud to share.

With a sleek hardtop and enhanced coupe foredeck seating/lounging zone, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is a brilliant entertaining platform and an inviting place to spend entire days on the water. Premium amenities, state-of-the-art technology and unrivaled performance - with your choice of sterndrive or inboard propulsion - combine to deliver a fully enjoyable cruising experience. Options for customization abound, meaning you can make the Coupe totally your own. And with a sleek, stylish aesthetic that's both gorgeously modern and unmistakably Sea Ray, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is a boat you'll be proud to own and proud to share.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Craftsmanship
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
A better cruise

When a marine engine generates energy, the boat’s design determines how efficiently that energy converts to forward motion. The Sundancer 350 Coupe’s hull is specifically designed to work with this transfer, actually amplifying the amount of usable energy for a smoother, more powerful ride. Sea Ray makes your boat work smarter not harder, so you can get the most out of your Sundancer.

 

Details matter

A car tire out of alignment—even by a fraction of an inch—forces the driver to constantly correct for a straight drive. Incorrect alignment by even a tenth of an inch on a boat causes the same disturbance in your ride’s smoothness and ease of handling. You shouldn’t have to settle on the water. Sea Ray uses cutting-edge robotic equipment to measure, cut and drill for engine placement that’s within four thousandths of an inch of true—about the thickness of a sheet of paper—to ensure every Sea Ray drives as perfectly as it was meant to.

 

The future of boating

Next Wave is an aggressive commitment to innovation across all Sea Ray platforms. The goal is nothing short of reimagining the boating experience again and again. By developing and championing new technologies such as Quiet Ride™, Dynamic Running Surface™ and Digital Dash™, and design breakthroughs including SkyFlow Design™, Sea Ray is asserting itself as the dominant global presence and a company of forward thinkers.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Design
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Bringing the outside in

The Sundancer 350 Coupe is designed for the outdoors, and its oversized hullside windows help bring the outside in, making the cabin airy and bright. Multi-tone accents and durable, marine-grade vinyl with UV-protection technology are more than just finishing touches on the Sundancer Series, they highlight Sea Ray’s signature style.

 

Space by design

The Sundancer 350 Coupe boasts impressive capacity for more entertaining and more memories thanks to clever design that maximizes onboard space and delivers more comforts than ever before. An extended swim platform and optional transom gourmet center bring the party all the way down to the water.

 

The Sea Ray way

Better materials make a better boat, and that’s why Sea Rays are the best. Teak accents elevate the stairs and footrest on the port lounge, while the helm is impeccably dressed for ergonomics and good looks. From the solid-surface wetbar countertop with stainless-steel trim to the enclosed interior head with a full fiberglass shower, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is done to the nines.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Features
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Delicious details

From the deluxe galley with ample storage to the solid-surface counter tops and recessed stove, the Sundancer 350 Coupe is fit for a top chef. The optional transom gourmet center can also accommodate a fridge, speakers, and built-in grill, so al fresco dining is both glamorous and convenient. Now, entertaining on your boat is easy as pie.

Sweet dreams

The Sundancer 350 Coupe’s V-berth comes fully equipped so you can rest easy. The double bed is outfitted with neutral sheets as well as a luxurious memory-foam mattress. Created by NASA, memory foam delivers undisturbed comfort for full rest. When you sleep well, you can wake up refreshed and ready for another beautiful day on the water.

Kings of comfort

The needs of you and your guests may change from outing to outing. That's why the Sundancer 350 Coupe includes Modelsiad spaces to settle in and get comfortable, from the inviting salon, to the mid-berth convertible twin beds, to the roomy V-berth with ample storage and an island-style double bed. Your boat's interior should fit your needs, and the Sundancer 350 Coupe is designed to do just that.

Stay onboard

Maximize your comfort on the water. The cabin's full fiberglass head features separate stalls for the shower and the head and sink, adding convenience when guests are aboard. Premium refinements and upscale fit and finish are pleasing to the eye and the touch, helping you make even more of a day of it, no matter how far you travel from the dock.

 

At the forefront of foredecks

Now this is clever: The Sundancer 350 Coupe features innovative new foredeck seating, expanding the usage possibilities beyond anything you've seen before on a coupe model. A recessed bow lounger seating system includes an articulating backrest, beverage holders and integral speakers. So you can enjoy the open air from a whole new perspective.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Warranty
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
Count on Sea Ray’s 3-Year Factory Warranty

One of the primary benefits of a new boat purchase is the freedom to relax, to put aside worry and focus on savoring the well-lived life on the water. Accordingly, Sea Ray is proud to offer a stellar 3-year factory warranty. This program, Sea Ray SENTIN3L, provides 3 years of enhanced coverage on every new cruiser, sport yacht and yacht in the Sea Ray lineup. The end result? Exceptional peace of mind.

All 2018 Sea Ray cruisers, sport yachts and yachts feature Sea Ray’s 3-year, bow-to-stern factory warranty on the boat and its components from defects in materials and workmanship. Additionally, gas engines are covered by a 5-year warranty backed by Mercury and Brunswick Product Protection, while diesel engines receive the coverage defined by their manufacturer. Finally, beyond the 3-year bow-to-stern coverage, all cruisers, sport yachts and yachts also have a 10-year Structural Hull Limited Warranty.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2018 Nautique GS20, Powered by a PCM ZR4 400 HP, Bimini with tower mounted surf pockets, Nautique awareness camera, One pair of 8.8 JL Audio M-Series speakers, Battery maintenance system, Platform and full boat cover, Fresh water engine flush system, Linc Panoray paddle wheel, Retractable ski pylon, Bow filler cushion, MX Series premier studio speakers, Surf select with surf switch, Ultra premium hand stitched leather steering wheel, Slide in air damn door

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description:
The GS20 blends masterful, award-winning designs from both the undisputed industry-leading G-Series and the world-record setting Ski Nautique Series into the ultimate 20-foot boat that’s sure to be a crowd pleaser for everyone. Loaded with new features, this boat has it all and then some! From the 12.4” Nautique LINC Panoray touchscreen and optional Nautique Awareness camera, to a new-age dash design and convenient transom seating, functionality and style meet ultimate versatility in 20 feet of perfection.

When you want to escape the confines of discipline-specific performance, the focus must not be on what you can’t have but on what you can. Viewing versatility as its own specialty, the Super Air Nautique GS20 transforms from a ski boat to a wake boat to a surf boat in a way that steps into a new realm of engineering, design and technology.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Hull
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Super Air Nautique GS20 is the first of its kind with a hull designed to optimize the wake and wave under running conditions for wakeboarding, wakesurfing, and waterskiing. Distinct characteristics taken from our world-record breaking Ski Nautique 200 begin at the bow transforming into features of our award-winning G-series at the transom. New technology in the Nautique Configurable Running Surface® (NCRS) has been developed for flawless performance at every speed and user setting. Select the Slalom Ski profile with NCRS Ski Assist to hit the course and fill 1,850 pounds of sub-floor internal ballast with Wake and Surf settings when you’re ready to go big.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Surf System
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The Nautique Surf System with Waveplate® comes standard on the Super Air Nautique GS20 giving the world’s most versatile towboat a world-class wave on demand. Integrating the Nautique Surf System into hull features inspired by our latest G-series, we are able to maximize wave size and push along with the ability to customize wave shape and initiate transfers at the touch of a button on the LINC PANORAY screen.

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Sound
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: Nautique brings you superior sound in the ultimate package by way of JL Audio components delivering the best sound systems in the industry. Rock your boat with 4 MX-series speakers standard on the Super Air Nautique GS20 or turn it up with the MX-Series Premier package featuring two additional speakers in the bow and a 10” subwoofer powered by a JL M600/6 amplifier. Keep it cranking behind the boat with the optional 7.7” or 8.8” JL M-Series tower speakers.

VehicleRemarketingBoat.GeneralBoatDescription: 2002 Mastercraft Pro Star 209, GM 5.7L, Tandem axle trailer with spare tire & loading guides, Cockpit & Bow cover, Wakeboard tower with racks & tower speakers, Teak swim platform, Ski pylon, Tilt steering wheel, Stereo with driver remote, Dual batteries with switch, Flip upbolster seat - ONLY 350 HOURS

AdditionalDetailDescription.Title: Manufacturer Provided Description
AdditionalDetailDescription.Description: The MasterCraft ProStar 209 is a wide, long, and well-performing direct-drive ski boat. At a full 20 feet, 11.5 inches with 96 inches of beam, the 209 features a sharp hull entry that knocks down lake chop and flattens it out at the transom. Interior comfort remains of high importance with seating for 12 including a lightweight, removable rear seat that fits four in comfort, and converts to a full-sized sunpad with plenty of room to sprawl out. The observer?s seat fits two full-sized adults and can accommodate a third with an optional flip-out addition. Plus, there?s enough room left over for seven other passengers. Up front, the bow meets and exceeds all the criteria for high-performance open bows: deep, wide, safe, and comfortable. On the exterior, this boat features a one-of-a-kind angled transom design, integrated platform, and hull flare. A wide, deep trunk, accessible by a dual-opening hatch, stores everything from skis to ropes to vests. Overloaded skiers will find storage help in big bunches underneath the passenger seat, rear seat and under each of the bow seats. Powered by a 310 horsepower fuel-injected engine, offering incredible low-end torque, smooth acceleration and rock-solid pulls, it's easy to reach high speeds in no time.
